If the SAL is used to save plugin settings, and XStream is used under the covers, there is no opportunity to do local 'class' aliasing.  If for example a class is used that is bundled inside a plugins2 plugin, no other plugin would necessarily be able to see it, eg BandanaEditor.

Currently I have a situation where the config settings are stored fine with:
{code}
pluginSettings.put(CONFIGURATION_KEY, configObj);
{code}

but Bandana editor barfs with:
{code}
...

class               : java.util.Map 
cause-exception     : com.thoughtworks.xstream.alias.CannotResolveClassException 
required-type       : java.util.TreeMap 
------------------------------- at /templates/bandana-editor-main.vm[line 38, column 45]
	at org.apache.velocity.runtime.parser.node.ASTMethod.handleInvocationException(ASTMethod.java:337)

...
{code}

Perhaps this is a question on how SAL handles classes that arent visibile globally, should it encode them somehow or should Bananda editor be a little brighter?

