It would be great if {toc-zone} macro would allow nested toc-zones...
You can face issues in generating toc-zone in case you start including pages into other pages.

1) Assume I have page A which defines toc-zone for the whole page. And I have page B which defines toc-zone for the whole page too. 
2) If I decide to include page B into page A using {include} macro, {toc-zone} get nested
   page A {toc-zone}
      page A content
      page B {toc-zone}
        page B content
      page B {toc-zone}
   page A {toc-zone}
3) and the result will be two wrong TOCs :-)

