In Confluence it's possible to label a bookmark for a colleague and have it appear in their bookmarks page.  However, bookmarks (including shared bookmarks) are bound by the permissions of the user's space.  It would be more consistent with the new social features if bookmarking worked like status updates, which are visible with members of your network regardless of your space permissions.

